=== (Fast)Battleship ((F)BB) ===
'''Note:'''
* BB have high firepower and use main guns to attack enemy ships.
* Day battle attack power cap can be reached easily with most battleships.
** The day damage softcap is 150. As most battleships can easily reach this cap, it is preferrable to focus on {{Hit}} stats instead.
* Can use artillery spotting to further increase attack.([[Aerial Combat|Air superiority required]])
** [[Artillery Spotting]] is a postcap multiplier that ignores the damage softcap. This allows you to deal even more damage during the day.
* [[Overweight Penalty and Fit Gun Bonus|Fit gun mechanics]] are drastically different on battleships in the sense that aside from bonuses, there are also penalties included for using overweight guns. Each ship class also have their own set of guns that are fit and overweight, check out [[Overweight Penalty and Fit Gun Bonus|this page]] for more information regarding this.
* Cannot attack submarines, even if you have {{Seaplane}}[http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/Seaplane#Seaplane_Bombers Bombers] equipped.
* Can equip {{RedAmmo}}[http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/List_of_Shells_by_stats#Armor_Piercing_Shells {{Tooltip|AP Shell|Armor Piercing Shell}}]
* The {{ShipLink|Italia|Roma Kai|text=V.V. Class Kai|link_class=Vittorio Veneto}}, {{ShipLink|Nagato Kai|Mutsu Kai|text=Nagato class Kai|link_class=Nagato}} and {{ShipLink|Yamato Kai|Musashi Kai|text=Yamato class Kai|link_class=Yamato}} are capable of carrying {{Seaplane}}[http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/Seaplane#Seaplane_Fighters Fighters]
* Only {{ShipLink|Italia}} and {{ShipLink|Roma Kai}} are capable of equipping {{Seaplane}}[http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/Seaplane#Seaplane_Bombers Bombers].
** Because of their poor slots, you are not recommended to use any {{Seaplane}}[http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/Seaplane#Seaplane_Bombers Bombers].

'''Points for equipment selection:'''
* Can you utilize artillery spotting?
* Do you want a Double Attack or a Cut In during day?
* Are you fighting against an installation?

