====Standard====
*{{RedGunHeavy}}Main Gun x2 +{{Seaplane}}Recon Seaplane + {{RedAmmo}} AP Shell
* The most used setup for battleships that allow both day cut-in and double attack.
* Base {{Firepower}} is excellent and also allows a decent night double attack.
* With two special attack types available, artillery spotting will have a higher activation rate.
* Cut-in (150% modifier) is useful against high armor enemies
* Also effective when facing Hard [[Installation]] targets.


====Standard Double Attack====
*{{RedGunHeavy}}Main Gun x2 +{{Seaplane}}Recon Seaplane + '''Wildcard'''
* Allows both day and night double attack
* Utilize the wildcard depending on what you need
** {{GreenAmmo}}[[Type 3 Shell|Type 3]] is to increase damage against soft [[Installation|installation-type]] enemies.
** {{Seaplane}}[http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/Seaplane#Seaplane_Fighters Fighters] if you need some support in establishing [[Aerial Combat|air superiority]].
** {{Radar}}[[Radar]] and {{Seaplane}}[http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/List_of_Seaplanes_by_stats#Reconnaissance_Seaplanes Recon] are alternatives if you lack {{RedAmmo}} or you don't want to use it for whatever reason.


====Night Battle Focus====
*{{RedGunHeavy}}Main Gun x2 + {{Seaplane}}[[Type 98 Reconnaissance Seaplane (Night Recon)|Night Recon]] '''OR''' Wildcard + {{Radar}}[[Radar]] '''OR''' Wildcard
* The setup for night battle focused maps.
* Since {{RedAmmo}} bonuses does not apply to night battles, it becomes less useful.
* Important for maps like [[5-3]]
* In case you don't have a {{Seaplane}}[[Type 98 Reconnaissance Seaplane (Night Recon)|Night Recon]], you can treat the slot as a wildcard.
* The wildcards can be anything, as long it's not a {{RedGunHeavy}} or {{YellowGun}}
